@node intro "Introduction to SMTPsend"

Welcome to SMTPsend V1.0
      
@{b}What is SMTPsend? @{ub}

Basically it allows you to use SMTPsend as an offline-email poster.

It  examines a given directory,  find all emails that have been  queued  to
there by SMTPsend and attempts to post them,  using SMTPsend.  It does this
the instant its run.

In  a  way its a replacement for SMTPd, although it doesn't wait around  in
memory and check the directory again later on as SMTPsend does.

@{b}Why did I write it? @{ub}

When  I  started using SMTPsend as an external mailer,  I wanted  to  write
email  off-line and post it  when I went on-line.  I tried using SMTPd  but
found  that this waits for a while before trying to send the queued  email,
which I didn't want. My program sends the email instantly and then quits.

@{b}Is if free? @{ub}

Yes.   It  is  copywrite so you can't alter it in  any  way.   It  must  be
destributed in the archive SMTPsend.lha which must contain...

	SMTPsend                  The executable
	SMTPsend.guide            What your reading now
	Changes.txt               Whats new in this version
	Warning.txt               Warning to previous users of SMTPsend


@endnode

@node install "Installing SMTPsend"

@{b}How do I install it?@{ub}

Its realy easy.  Simply put the program file (thats SMTPsend)  anywhere you
want.  SMTPpost @{b}must@{ub} also be in the same directory,  otherwise  it
won't work!

Most  people  are already using SMTPpost so they just put SMTPsend  in  the
same directory.

Thats all there is to it.

@endnode             

@node using "Using SMTPsend"

@{b}Using SMTPsend@{ub}

@{i}SMTPsend [-l] <maildir> [-m <movedir]@{ui}

-l  Switches on the logging.  A defualt logfile SMTPsend.log will be opened
in  the directory the program is run.  You cannot specify the name  of  the
logfile.

<maildir> The directory where the emails are stored.

-m  causes  emails to be moved to <movedir> instead of being deleted  after
being sent.

@{b}Examples@{ub}

 SMTPsend Work:Mailspool/

 - Will send all email in Work:Mailspool and delete them when their sent.

 
 SMTPsend -l Work:Mailspool/

 - Same as above but will write results to SMTPsend.log


 SMTPsend -l Work:Mailspool/ -m Work:Sentmail/

 - Send all emails in Work:Mailsool/ and move sent ones to Work:Sentmail/
   Also write to the logfile SMTPsend.log

@endnode

